"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444569","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-20","<p>At the Summer Budget 2015 the government launched a consultation on whether there is a case for reforming pensions tax relief to strengthen incentives to save and offer savers greater simplicity and transparency, or whether it would be best to keep with the current system. The government is considering the response and will publish a response at Budget 2016.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-20T16:28:54.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444569/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444569/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444569/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-13","Pensions: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of introducing flat rate tax relief on pensions contributions.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","22274"
