"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444772","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-21","<p>Specific legislation prohibiting the use of laser pens against aircraft has been in place since 2009. Under Article 222 of the Air Navigation Order (2009), it is an offence to<em> “</em>direct or shine any light at any aircraft in flight so as to dazzle or distract the pilot of the aircraft”<em>.</em> Breaches of this article can be punished by a fine of up to £2500.</p><br /><p>In addition, under Article 137, it is an offence to <em>“</em>recklessly or negligently act in a manner likely to endanger an aircraft, or any person in an aircraft”. If convicted, offenders could face up to a maximum penalty of five years in prison.</p><br /><p>The Civil Aviation Authority (CAA), as the independent safety regulator, has established a working group with relevant public and industry participants to consider what further measures may help counter the threat from the misuse of laser pens. The Government will continue to monitor closely the outcome of this work.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-01-21T15:35:02.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444772/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444772/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444772/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-13","Aviation: Lasers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to ban the use of laser pen technology in proximity to aircraft and airports.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","22448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444773","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-21","<p>THINK! supports pedestrian road safety education though engaging intermediaries – e.g. teachers, road safety professionals &amp; parents - who are able to deliver road safety messages using free resources, to children and teenagers in a credible and impactful way. THINK! is reviewing their education offer in order to ensure materials and road safety messages are up-to-date and relevant for the current generation.</p><p> </p><p>THINK! is also working closely with partners at the RAC and the Scouts Association to develop road safety resources for out-of-school groups, to ensure road safety is continued to be taught in and outside the classroom.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is providing £50 million over the next four years to support Bikeability cycle training in schools in England (outside London). This funding will help to increase children's road awareness, encourage active travel and improve future motorists’ empathy for more vulnerable road users.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-21T15:38:58.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444773/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444773/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444773/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-13","Roads: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department plans to take in 2016 to ensure that young people under 16 understand road safety issues from the perspectives of pedestrians, cyclists and car users.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","22451"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444775","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>Legacy benefit entitlement will cease when a claimant starts a claim for Universal Credit. We have put in place specific arrangements which allow a person transferring to Universal Credit to apply for an advance on their first UC payment.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-19T14:51:43.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444775/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444775/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444775/answer","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444775/answer/previousversion/39692","Biography information for Priti Patel","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what his policy is on the continuation of payments for legacy benefits to claimants being transferred to universal credit until a first universal credit payment is received.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","22230"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444776","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>Everyone eligible for a Christmas bonus will receive their payment in full. A technical error meant that 327,379 people had a delayed payment.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-19T10:02:55.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444776/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444776/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444776/answer","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444776/answer/previousversion/39698","Biography information for Priti Patel","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Christmas Bonus","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people who were eligible to receive a Christmas bonus on their benefits had not received it on 24 December 2015.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","22231"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444777","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>There are 2,006 employees on fixed term contracts out of a workforce of 84,429, which equates to 2.4%.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-19T11:43:47.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444777/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444777/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444777/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Department for Work and Pensions: Conditions of Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of staff working in his Department are employees on fixed-term contracts.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","22249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444778","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-18","<p>I refer my Rt. Hon. Member to the answer I gave on the 11 January 2016 <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;use-dates=True&amp;answered-from=2014-12-29&amp;answered-to=2016-01-15&amp;dept=29&amp;uin=21335" target="_blank">UIN21335</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-18T17:09:05.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444778/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444778/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444778/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Universal Credit: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the statement in his Department's press release of 1 November 2011, entitled Iain Duncan Smith sets out next steps for moving claimants onto universal credit, on what dates since 1 November 2011 his Department has calculated the proportion of new technology required to deliver universal credit which is complete; and what that proportion was on each of those dates.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","22246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444779","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>The information requested is not available.</p><p>The number of people on benefits is driven by a range of factors. Because of this, the programme measures progress by the successful achievement of its delivery plan rather than numbers of claimants. <br></p>","Witham","Priti Patel","22332","2016-01-19T15:08:26.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444779/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444779/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444779/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Universal Credit: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many lone parent households that are in receipt of housing benefit will be affected by changes to universal credit work allowances in (a) Burnley, (b) Lancashire and (c) the North West.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","22323"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444780","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-22","<br /><table><tbody><tr><td>Responsibility Centre</td><td>Number of WC’s</td></tr><tr><td>JCNW Burnley JC Plus</td><td>19</td></tr><tr><td>Lancashire</td><td>235</td></tr><tr><td>JCNW North West England</td><td>1436</td></tr></tbody></table><p>The information available for the number of Employment and Support Allowance claimants by phase of claim and geography is published and can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp</a></p><p>Guidance for users is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp</a></p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel","22324","2016-01-22T11:42:37.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444780/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444780/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444780/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Jobcentre Plus: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many work coaches are employed by job centres in (a) Burnley, (b) Lancashire and (c) the North West.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","22322"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444781","Department for Work and Pensions","true","2016-01-19","<p>The Department has two Personal Independence Payment (PIP) contracts with Atos, each covering a geographical area. North of England &amp; Scotland (Lot 1) has a value of £206,703,507. London &amp; South of England (Lot 3) has a value of £183,894,556.</p><br /><p>There are a number of Service Levels (Key Performance Indicators are not used in PIP contracts) which Atos are required to deliver to meet the Department’s service requirements. These are detailed in the attached Annex 1. In addition, a number of interim Service Levels have been introduced to address specific performance targets.</p><br /><p>In the event Atos fail to achieve a key service level, contracts provide for Service Credits to be applied. Service Credits are a contractual remedy applied to Atos to recognise the loss of service received and to ensure any performance issues are rectified quickly.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-19T12:10:53.773Z","2016-01-26T17:27:46.46Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444781/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444781/answer","22348 Annex 1.docx","22348 Annex 1.docx","Annex 1","Annex 1","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444781/answer","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444781/answer/previousversion/39773","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Department for Work and Pensions: Atos Healthcare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the value is of the personal independence payment assessment contract with ATOS; what the main key performance indicators (KPIs) are under that contract; and what the (a) financial and (b) other penalties are for failure to meet KPIs.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","22348"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444782","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-18","<p>A home consultation can be offered, in particular where a claimant is unable to travel to a consultation as a result of their health condition or impairment. Home visits are offered when the claimant provides confirmation via their own health professional which indicates that they are unable to travel on health grounds or at a claimant’s request where the assessment provider’s health professional determines this is appropriate for their health condition or disability.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-18T16:55:52.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444782/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444782/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444782/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Work Capability Assessment: Location","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he has taken to enable applicants who have suffered from a stroke, heart attack or any other major health scare to access a work capability assessment of medical assessment within a 90 minute journey.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","22424"
