"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444786","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-22","<p>The information requested regarding income support is published and available at:</p><br /><p><a href="http://tabulation-tool.dwp.gov.uk/100pc/tabtool.html" target="_blank">http://tabulation-tool.dwp.gov.uk/100pc/tabtool.html</a></p><br /><p>Guidance on how to extract the information can be found at:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance</a></p><br /><p>Statistics on the claimant count, which shows the number of Jobseeker’s Allowance claimants, can be found at:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp</a></p><br /><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel","22334","2016-01-22T14:28:06.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444786/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444786/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444786/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Jobseeker's Allowance: Burnley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Burnley receive income-based jobseeker's allowance.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","22335"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444787","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-21","<p>The single rate of the Savings Credit threshold will rise by 5.8 per cent and the couple rate by 5.5 per cent in April 2016; anyone in receipt of Savings Credit will be affected by this change. The latest estimates of Pension Credit recipients split by those in receipt of Guarantee Credit only, Guarantee Credit and Savings Credit, and Savings Credit only are available from the DWP tabtool:</p><p><a href="http://tabulation-tool.dwp.gov.uk/100pc/tabtool.html" target="_blank">http://tabulation-tool.dwp.gov.uk/100pc/tabtool.html</a></p><p>The actual impact of up-rating on someone’s Pension Credit depends on a variety of factors, including the make-up of their other income and how or if it increases annually. For example, the basic State Pension will be increased with earnings under the “triple lock”, and the Standard Minimum Guarantee in Pension Credit will also be increased with earnings. Those in receipt of Savings Credit should be better off overall from April 2016 if their State Pension or other income increases.</p><br /> <br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-21T09:59:02.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444787/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444787/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444787/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Pension Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of how many people will receive a lower pension credit entitlement as a result of the rise of the single saving credit threshold by 5.8 per cent and of the couples' threshold by 5.5 per cent.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","22382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444788","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-18","<p>The winter fuel payment eligibility criteria for people who normally live in the EEA, was changed for winter 2015-16. A temperature criterion was introduced by the DWP using information from a report it commissioned from the Met Office. This report showed the average winter temperature data for each EEA country and Switzerland and for the regions of the UK. The Met Office report was produced in 2012 and used information from a dataset for the reference period 1961-1990 available through the Climatic Research Unit of the University of East Anglia.</p><br /><p>The average winter temperature in the warmest part of the UK, the South West, is 5.6<sup>o</sup>C. This point is the basis for the changes made to the winter fuel payment eligibility criteria. People living in countries with an average winter temperature of no more than 5.6<sup>o</sup>C, or a temperature that is close enough to that to be statistically equivalent, are eligible for a winter fuel payment.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-18T12:31:55.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444788/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444788/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444788/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Winter Fuel Payments: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the results were of temperature tests to determine eligibility to receive winter fuel allowance of people living abroad in 2015.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","22383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444789","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-18","<p>The winter fuel payment eligibility criteria for people who normally live in the EEA, was changed for winter 2015-16. A temperature criterion was introduced by the DWP using information from a report it commissioned from the Met Office. This report showed the average winter temperature data for each EEA country and Switzerland and for the regions of the UK. The Met Office report was produced in 2012 and used information from a dataset for the reference period 1961-1990 available through the Climatic Research Unit of the University of East Anglia.</p><br /><p>The average winter temperature in the warmest part of the UK, the South West, is 5.6<sup>o</sup>C. This point is the basis for the changes made to the winter fuel payment eligibility criteria. People living in countries with an average winter temperature of no more than 5.6<sup>o</sup>C, or a temperature that is close enough to that to be statistically equivalent, are eligible for a winter fuel payment.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-18T12:35:53.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444789/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444789/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444789/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Winter Fuel Payments: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many temperature tests there were to determine eligibility to receive winter fuel allowance of people living abroad in 2015.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","22384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444790","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-22","<p>All Jobcentre Work Coaches complete learning that has been designed specifically for their role. This learning combines the knowledge, skills and behaviours they need to coach claimants effectively so that they are able to identify for themselves what they need to do to find work and how best to do it.</p><p>It includes diversity and equality, working with vulnerable claimants and working with claimants who have a mental health condition.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-22T11:28:20.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444790/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444790/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444790/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Jobcentre Plus: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what training jobcentre work coaches receive.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","22329"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444791","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-21","<p>As part of the assistance being provided under Universal Support, Universal Credit gives budgeting support to help claimants manage their money on a monthly basis and pay bills on time.</p><p>As well as support offered by work coaches, claimants are offered advice by external organisations with the relevant expertise. This advice is available online, by phone or face-to-face.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-21T10:19:12.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444791/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444791/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444791/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Universal Credit: Advisory Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what personal budgeting advice, and in what format, is provided to recipients of universal credit.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","22328"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444792","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-25","<p>The UK already provides comprehensive employment and social protection for workers, including domestic workers. This includes the right to National Minimum Wage, right to work a maximum number of hours a week, paid holiday, health &amp; safety protections, maternity/paternity leave and the right to be protected from discrimination.</p><p>These core rights are enforced for <strong>all </strong>workers who are legally entitled to work in the UK. The Government is also focused on improving protection for vulnerable domestic workers by ensuring that immigration and border staff are trained to recognise potential victims of abuse; that overseas domestic workers are provided with guidance on their rights and how to obtain help; and that employers know their responsibilities.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-01-25T16:21:58.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444792/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444792/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444792/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-13","Domestic Service: Treaties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether his Department is taking steps to implement International Labour Convention No.189 on Domestic Workers.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","22511"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444793","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>The information you have requested is not currently available.</p><br /><p>During 2016 we will be increasing the range of statistics on Universal Credit which will be published in accordance with the relevant protocols in the Code of Practice for Official Statistics.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-19T10:28:30.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444793/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444793/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444793/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many benefit claimants who are considered by his Department to have a limited capability to work are in receipt of universal credit in (a) Burnley, (b) Lancashire and (c) the UK.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","22331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444794","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>There are two Universal Credit service centres in the North West - Bolton and Makerfield.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-19T10:24:27.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444794/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444794/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444794/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Universal Credit: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many universal credit switch centres there are in (a) Burnley, (b) Lancashire and (c) the North West.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","22330"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444795","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>The number of computers available in jobcentres for recipients to access benefits online are as follows:</p><br /><p>Burnley 6</p><p>Lancashire 191</p><p>North West 474</p><br /><p>In addition, claimants who do not have their own internet access can be signposted to local services such as libraries or local authority facilities.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-19T15:03:57.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444795/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444795/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444795/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Jobcentres: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many computers each jobcentre in (a) Burnley, (b) Lancashire and (c) the North West has available for recipients of universal credit to access benefits online.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","22326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444796","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-22","<p>People without digital skills will be offered support to make and manage their Universal Credit (UC) claim online, to acquire and to improve their digital skills. This help will be provided by work coaches in Jobcentres and by Local Authorities and other partner organisations via the ‘Universal Support delivered locally’ programme.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-22T11:20:20.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444796/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444796/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444796/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what provision there is for ICT training for recipients of universal credit.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","22327"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444797","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-22","<br /><table><tbody><tr><td>Responsibility Centre</td><td>Number of WC’s</td></tr><tr><td>JCNW Burnley JC Plus</td><td>19</td></tr><tr><td>Lancashire</td><td>235</td></tr><tr><td>JCNW North West England</td><td>1436</td></tr></tbody></table><p>The information available for the number of Employment and Support Allowance claimants by phase of claim and geography is published and can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp</a></p><p>Guidance for users is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/home/newuser.asp</a></p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel","22322","2016-01-22T11:42:38.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444797/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444797/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444797/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Social Security Benefits: Burnley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many benefit claimants considered by his Department to have a limited capability to work live in Burnley.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","22324"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444798","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>According to the latest published statistics, there were 1,136 Universal Credit claimants in Burnley in November 2015.</p><br /><p>This information can be found at the following link:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/universal-credit-29-apr-2013-to-3-dec-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/universal-credit-29-apr-2013-to-3-dec-2015</a></p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-19T14:58:51.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444798/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444798/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444798/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Universal Credit: Burnley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Burnley are in receipt of universal credit.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","22325"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444799","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-20","<p>As at the end of August 2015, there were 3,130 exemptions to Application Fees<strong>. </strong></p><p><strong></strong></p><p>There are no exemptions for collection and enforcement charges.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p>More details can be found on page 4 of the Child Maintenance Scheme quarterly summary of statistics which can be accessed online at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/2012-statutory-child-maintenance-scheme-aug-2013-to-aug-2015-experimental" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/2012-statutory-child-maintenance-scheme-aug-2013-to-aug-2015-experimental</a>.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-20T10:01:44.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444799/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444799/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444799/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many parents have been exempted from fees and charges for the 2012 child maintenance scheme.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","22381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444800","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-20","<p>As at the end of August 2015, 82,600 cases were paying via Direct Pay.</p><br /><p>More details can be found on page 6 of the Child Maintenance Scheme quarterly summary of statistics which can be accessed online at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/2012-statutory-child-maintenance-scheme-aug-2013-to-aug-2015-experimental" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/2012-statutory-child-maintenance-scheme-aug-2013-to-aug-2015-experimental</a>.</p><p>Notes:</p><ol><li>This figure only includes cases that are live with a payment that is due.</li><li>Figures are rounded to the nearest 100.</li></ol>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-20T10:06:05.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444800/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444800/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444800/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many parents have moved to direct pay since the introduction of the 2012 child maintenance scheme.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","22378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444801","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-20","<p>The level of the application charge and collection charges for parents with care and non-resident parents will be included in the statutory 30 month review of charging, which is due to be completed by December 2016. There are no current plans to increase the application fee or collection charges.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","22380","2016-01-20T10:09:49.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444801/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444801/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444801/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans he has to increase collection charges for the 2012 child maintenance scheme for the (a) parent with care and (b) non-resident parent.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","22379"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444802","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-20","<p>The level of the application charge and collection charges for parents with care and non-resident parents will be included in the statutory 30 month review of charging, which is due to be completed by December 2016. There are no current plans to increase the application fee or collection charges.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","22379","2016-01-20T10:09:49.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444802/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444802/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444802/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans he has to increase application charges to join the 2012 child maintenance scheme.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","22380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444803","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>The government has to date spent approximately £53,000 on legal costs associated with the case of Hurley and Others v Secretary of State for Work and Pensions [2015]</p><p>It should be noted that this figure includes VAT where this is payable (e.g. on Counsel’s fees) but do not include costs attributable to the time spent by government advisory lawyers on these cases. Time spent by such advisory lawyers is not recorded in a manner that allows it to be attributed to individual cases. Nor does it include any costs payable by the Secretary of State to the other parties to these cases or received from the other parties.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-19T12:23:57.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444803/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444803/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444803/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Department for Work and Pensions: Legal Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what his Department's legal costs were in Ashley Hurley, Mary Jarrett and Lee Palmer v Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, CO/2717/2014 and CO/3220/2014.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","22377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444804","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>Disability premium is an extra amount automatically added to Income Support or income-based Jobseeker’s Allowance (JSA) for those who qualify.</p><br /><p>Information on the payment of this premium for those who were also receiving Disability Living Allowance (DLA) and have now transferred to Personal Independence Payment (PIP) is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-19T12:01:14.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444804/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444804/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444804/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Personal Independence Payment: Disability Premium","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people no longer receive the disability premium following their transfer from receipt of disability living allowance to personal independence payments.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","22434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444805","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-19","<p>When someone makes a claim to Universal Credit they are advised of the verification needed to receive the Housing Element of Universal Credit. This is re-iterated when the claimant is contacted to book their initial interview at the Jobcentre.</p><br />","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-01-19T10:10:33.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444805/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444805/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444805/answer","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444805/answer/previousversion/39701","Biography information for Priti Patel","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-13","Universal Credit: Housing Associations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether universal credit applicants who are housing association tenants are informed upon application of the need for a letter from their landlord in order to receive housing cost assistance; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","22473"
