"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444120","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-19","<p>Former Ministers and former civil servants are subject to rules that cover the acceptance of all outside appointments and employment after they leave public office. Information about which former Ministers and former civil servants have failed to consult ACoBA before taking up an appointment is not held. It is individuals’ own responsibility to ensure that they comply with the requirements of these rules.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","22194","2016-01-19T13:25:46.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444120/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444120/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444120/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-12","Lord Barker of Battle","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what advice his Department issued to Baron Barker of Battle about his appointment to the British Photovoltaic Association.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","22073"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444121","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-22","<p>The Cabinet Office has regular ongoing communications with the National Archives.</p><p>The Minister for the Cabinet Office met National Archive officials to discuss the release of Cabinet Office papers for the 1986 to 1988 period on two occasions.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","22436","2016-02-22T15:39:44.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444121/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444121/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444121/answer","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444121/answer/previousversion/39673","Biography information for Matt Hancock","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-12","Cabinet Papers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what recent communications his Department has had with the National Archives on the release of Cabinet papers dated between 1986 and 1988.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","22110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444122","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-18","<p>To ensure fair and open competition the Government does not publish the names of bidders during the tender process.</p><p>Successful bidders for all central government contracts are published on Contracts Finder:</p><p><a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search" target="_blank">https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Search</a></p><p>Successful bidders for all Crown Commercial Service (CCS) contracts are published on the CCS web site:</p><p><a href="http://ccs-agreements.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/" target="_blank">http://ccs-agreements.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/</a></p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-01-18T09:28:52.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444122/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444122/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444122/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-12","Cabinet Office: G4S","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which contracts with his Department G4S are currently bidding for.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","22109"
