"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444227","Department of Health","false","2016-01-20","<p>No such assessment has been made. The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) is currently appraising nivolumab (Opdivo) for squamous non-small cell lung cancer and has not yet issued its final guidance.</p><br /><p>In developing its technology appraisal guidance, NICE works closely with stakeholders, including manufacturers. NICE’s consultation on its draft guidance closed on 19 January 2016.</p><br /><p>In the absence of NICE guidance, it is for commissioners to make funding decisions based on the available evidence.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","22164","2016-01-20T12:20:03.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444227/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444227/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444227/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","Lung Cancer: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the effect of the negative interim NICE Appraisal Committee Decision on nivolumab for squamous non-small cell lung cancer on patients.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","22162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444228","Department of Health","false","2016-01-20","<p>NHS England has advised that it understands that the manufacturer of nivolumab (Opdivo), Bristol-Myers Squibb, received 73 registrations for nivolumab for locally advanced or metastatic squamous non-small cell lung cancer through the Early Access to Medicines Scheme before the scientific opinion expired in July 2015. A geographical breakdown of this figure is not available.</p><br /><p>NHS England does not currently fund nivolumab for metastatic squamous non-small cell lung cancer and has advised that its funding position will be determined by the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence’s final technology appraisal guidance which is expected in May 2016. Further information is available at:</p><br /><p><a href="http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/indevelopment/gid-tag506" target="_blank">www.nice.org.uk/guidance/indevelopment/gid-tag506</a></p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-01-20T12:28:41.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444228/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444228/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444228/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","Lung Cancer: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many patients are receiving nivolumab for locally advanced or metastatic squamous non-small cell lung cancer in (a) England and (b) Strangford; and when NICE plans to complete its appraisal of that drug.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","22163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444229","Department of Health","false","2016-01-20","<p>No such assessment has been made. The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) is currently appraising nivolumab (Opdivo) for squamous non-small cell lung cancer and has not yet issued its final guidance.</p><br /><p>In developing its technology appraisal guidance, NICE works closely with stakeholders, including manufacturers. NICE’s consultation on its draft guidance closed on 19 January 2016.</p><br /><p>In the absence of NICE guidance, it is for commissioners to make funding decisions based on the available evidence.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","22162","2016-01-20T12:20:03.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444229/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444229/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444229/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","Nivolumab","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will request that NICE work with the manufacturers of nivolumab to ensure patients with lung cancer can access that medicine at the earliest opportunity.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","22164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444230","Department of Health","false","2016-01-20","<p>The manufacturing process for aseptic pharmaceutical products by licensed Specials manufacturers is subject to Good Manufacturing Practice and Good Pharmacovigilance Practice – both of which are monitored by the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p>Aseptic compounding in pharmacies and health clinics under the section 10 exemption of the Medicines Act 1968 is carried out under the supervision of a pharmacist and is subject to periodic audits by National Health Service quality assurance pharmacists.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-01-20T12:42:54.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444230/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444230/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444230/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","Pharmacy: Negligence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to reduce errors in the dispensing of aseptic pharmaceutical products.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","22179"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444231","Department of Health","false","2016-01-20","<p>Neither the Department nor NHS England has made any such assessment.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-01-20T12:15:04.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444231/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444231/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444231/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","Pharmacy: Negligence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the level of aseptic pharmaceutical medication error within the NHS.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","22180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444232","Department of Health","false","2016-01-20","<p>The Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency is working with other groups to promote the risk-reducing benefits of dose banding.</p><br /><p>NHS England, through its Medicines Optimisation Clinical Reference Group work programme, is working with key stakeholders to identify/agree national standard dose bands for chemotherapy. A national Commissioning for Quality and Innovation goal has been agreed to support the implementation of the dose bands during 2017-18.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-01-20T12:40:06.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444232/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444232/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444232/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","Pharmacy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether his Department has a policy on standardising the dose branding of aseptic pharmaceutical products across all health trusts.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","22181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444233","Department of Health","false","2016-01-20","<p>Where appropriate, automation has a role to play in ensuring consistent output from aseptic compounding and increased production capacity. It may also provide additional protection against microbiological contamination by use of ‘closed systems’ of manufacture.</p><br /><p>Licensed specials manufacturers may consider automation as an appropriate solution for their product range and capacity. In these cases, Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency inspections assess whether the process design, validation, personnel, training and procedures relating to the automated system comply with the requirements of Good Manufacturing Practice.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-01-20T12:34:51.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444233/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444233/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444233/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","Pharmacy: Negligence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the potential role of technology in reducing aseptic pharmaceutical medication error.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","22182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444234","Department of Health","false","2016-01-20","<p>NHS England is working with local authorities, clinicians, patient representatives and Public Health England to consider the clinical and cost effectiveness of providing pre-exposure prophylaxis (PrEP) to at-risk groups to prevent them acquiring HIV. The PrEP clinical policy proposition is one of many going through NHS England’s 2016/17 prioritisation round.</p><br /><p>In July 2015 NHS England approved a significant new investment in a ‘Treatment as Prevention’ programme to help reduce transmissions from persons known to be HIV positive.</p><br /><p>We have made no estimates of the number of people accessing PrEP through private provision.</p><br />","Battersea","Jane Ellison","22188","2016-01-20T16:10:20.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444234/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444234/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444234/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","HIV Infection: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, when HIV Pre-Exposure Prophylaxis will be made available on the NHS to men who have sex with men.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","22187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444235","Department of Health","false","2016-01-20","<p>NHS England is working with local authorities, clinicians, patient representatives and Public Health England to consider the clinical and cost effectiveness of providing pre-exposure prophylaxis (PrEP) to at-risk groups to prevent them acquiring HIV. The PrEP clinical policy proposition is one of many going through NHS England’s 2016/17 prioritisation round.</p><br /><p>In July 2015 NHS England approved a significant new investment in a ‘Treatment as Prevention’ programme to help reduce transmissions from persons known to be HIV positive.</p><br /><p>We have made no estimates of the number of people accessing PrEP through private provision.</p><br />","Battersea","Jane Ellison","22187","2016-01-20T16:10:20.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444235/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444235/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444235/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","HIV Infection: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of people in England accessing HIV Pre-Exposure Prophylaxis through private provision.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","22188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444236","Department of Health","false","2016-01-18","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to the hon. Member for High Peak (Andrew Bingham) on 2 December 2015 to <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-12-02/18482/" target="_blank">Question 18482</a>.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-01-18T10:52:29.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444236/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444236/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444236/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","NHS","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department took to publicise the recent NHS Mandate Consultation.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","22200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444237","Department of Health","false","2016-01-20","<p>In April 2015, NHS England advised System Resilience Groups that all resilience initiatives started in response to the 2014-15 document should continue, and were also informed of new resilience planning priorities for the coming year. A copy of the letter is attached.</p><br /><p>For this year, funding was given to NHS Employers to support flu vaccination communications aimed at staff working in care homes, and to work with National Health Service trusts with low staff vaccination uptake by providing support networks and events.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-01-20T17:37:51.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444237/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444237/answer","pq22193 letter.pdf ; pq22193 document.xlsx","pq22193 letter.pdf ; pq22193 document.xlsx","Letter ; NHS England Publications Gateway Reference","Letter ; NHS England Publications Gateway Reference","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444237/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the status is of Operational Resilience Capacity Planning for 2014-15; and what the status is of the retained funding for flu vaccinations for clinicians in the independent sector.","false","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","22193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444238","Department of Health","false","2016-03-22","<p>The table attached shows average median waiting times in weeks to start consultant-led elective treatment for National Health Service commissioning organisations and regions which most closely match those requested.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-03-22T16:34:21.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444238/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444238/answer","PQ22210 Table.xlsx","PQ22210 Table.xlsx","Average median waiting times table","Average median waiting times table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444238/answer","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444238/answer/previousversion/39705","Biography information for Jane Ellison","17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","Hospitals: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the average hospital waiting time was for NHS patients in (a) Barnsley East constituency, (b) Barnsley, (c) South Yorkshire and (d) Yorkshire and the Humber since 2010.","false","Biography information for Michael Dugher","Barnsley East","Michael Dugher","22210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444239","Department of Health","false","2016-01-18","<p>The number of occasions when there was an agreed temporary divert of patients from hospitals in Barnsley, South Yorkshire and Yorkshire and the Humber to other accident and emergency departments is available from NHS England’s winter daily situation reports, which are collected from acute trusts each weekday during winter only. Published figures can be found using the following link.</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/winter-daily-sitreps/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/winter-daily-sitreps/</a></p><br />","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-01-18T11:14:29.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444239/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444239/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444239/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","Accident and Emergency Departments: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many incidents of accident and emergency departments diverting admissions to other hospitals there were in (a) Barnsley East constituency, (b) Barnsley, (c) South Yorkshire and (d) Yorkshire and the Humber in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Michael Dugher","Barnsley East","Michael Dugher","22211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444240","Department of Health","false","2016-01-18","<p>NHS England with support from the Association of Directors of Adult Social Services, is visiting a selection of areas to talk to clinical commissioning groups and local authorities about their Autism Diagnostic Care Pathways. Based on information provided in the most recent local authority Autism Self-Assessment exercise, the areas selected include those areas that have assessed themselves as having a diagnostic pathway in place, those who appear to be facing obstacles, and those who have no pathway in place. A report on the work will be completed by the end of April 2016.</p><br /><p><strong></strong></p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-01-18T12:55:40.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444240/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444240/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-01-12","Mental Health Services: Autism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 7 January 2016 to Question 20755, when the visits to clinical commissioning groups referred to in that question are planned to start; and when he expects the findings of such visits to be reported to him.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","22206"
