"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444283","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-18","<br /><p>Since the launch of the Armed Forces Covenant in 2011 the Ministry of Defence has worked closely with Northern Ireland Government Departments, Service charities and other groups to build on existing measures to support the Armed Forces Community. In 2013, the Select Committee on Northern Ireland Affairs reported that, less some specific areas, Covenant measures were being applied in Northern Ireland.</p><br /><p>I acknowledge that the Armed Forces Covenant does not enjoy the same level of awareness or appreciation in Northern Ireland as in other parts of the UK. However, I am clear that every effort is being made to implement the Covenant against the particular nuances of the Northern Irish political and legal environment. The Ministry of Defence and other parties work tirelessly to ensure good relationships help develop improved understanding of specific needs and I have been impressed by the way in which solutions to these needs are generated in a focussed and professional manner. Such provision is fully commensurate with the aims and objectives of the Covenant, whether it is branded as such or not.</p><br /><p>Service personnel in Northern Ireland are well-catered for under the auspices of the Covenant and are at no particular disadvantage, although more work is needed to identify the needs of those within the veterans community. This work is ongoing, well-resourced, and fully recognised as activity provided within the scope of the Armed Forces Covenant.</p><br /><br />","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","22172 ; 22173","2016-01-18T15:59:18.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444283/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444283/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444283/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-12","Armed Forces Covenant: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the reasons for delays in the full implementation of the Armed Forces Covenant in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Gavin Robinson","Belfast East","Gavin Robinson","22174"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444284","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-01-19","<p>The Government is in discussion with the Governments of the Overseas Territories on their plans to improve company transparency. The Territories have agreed to hold beneficial ownership information in central registers or similarly effective systems. Such systems will need to meet the following criteria: a) UK law enforcement and tax authorities must be able to access company beneficial ownership information without restriction, subject to relevant safeguards; b) These competent authorities should be able to quickly identify all companies that a particular beneficial owner has a stake in without needing to submit multiple and repeated requests; and c) Companies or their beneficial owners must not be alerted to the fact that an investigation is underway.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-01-19T16:30:31.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444284/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444284/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444284/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-01-12","British Overseas Territories: Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the (a) number and (b) quality of Overseas Territories' adoptions of public registers of beneficial ownership since his meetings with them on 15 June 2013 and his letter to them on 24 April 2014.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","22027"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444285","Scotland Office","false","2016-01-18","<p>As at 31 December 2015, there were 32 men and 27 women working in the Scotland Office.</p><p>Information on staff gender breakdown by grade in the Scotland Office for previous years is published in the Office’s annual reports. The latest annual report for 2014-15 is available in the House of Commons Library.</p><br /> <br />","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-01-18T12:36:10.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444285/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444285/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444285/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-01-12","Scotland Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many people of each gender work in his Department.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","22067"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444286","Scotland Office","false","2016-01-20","<p>In the period since the Smith Commission, the UK and Scottish Governments have had regular meetings to discuss issues relating to asylum seekers. These have included discussions on the non-legislative proposals from the Commission, and a demonstration for Scottish Government officials of the asylum process at the Home Office in Glasgow. This cross-government work with the Scottish Government on asylum issues is on-going.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-01-20T16:11:08.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444286/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444286/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444286/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-01-12","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, pursuant to the Statement of 11 January 2016 on the Smith Commission Agreement, HCWS458, what the (a) dates, (b) minutes and (c) outcomes was of any discussions or meeting held since 28 November 2014 on issues relating to asylum seekers with (i) Home Office Ministers and (ii) Ministers or Officials of the Scottish Government.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","22198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444287","Scotland Office","false","2016-01-18","<p>I have regular discussions with the Scottish Government’s Deputy First Minister on all aspects of the Smith Commission Agreement, the UK and Scottish Governments have had a number of meetings to discuss this issue and my written ministerial statement was shared with the Scottish Government in advance of publication. Scotland Office Ministers and officials also have regular discussions with further and higher education institutions and representative organisations such as Universities Scotland.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2016-01-18T15:35:06.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444287/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444287/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444287/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2016-01-12","Higher Education: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, pursuant to the Written Statement of 11 January 2016, HCWS458, what steps his Government has taken to implement the Smith Commission's recommendation to explore the possibility of introducing formal schemes to allow international higher education students graduating from Scottish further and higher education institutions to remain in Scotland and contribute to economic activity for a defined period of time; whether he has consulted with Scottish further and higher education institutions on this matter; and (c) for what reasons his Department has not discussed this matter with the Scottish Government.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","22102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444288","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-18","<p>Pursuant to the Answer of 11 January 2016 to Question 21125, the Department for Transport remains fully committed to our modernisation programme of over 850 miles of electrification. Over 50 miles have already been completed since 2010 compared to just 10 miles electrified in the 13 years of Labour Government from 1997.</p><br /><p>Some schemes are more immature in their development and, whilst schemes in this category will have significant delivery within Control Period 5, these schemes will span more than one control period.</p><br /><p>It will be for Network Rail to determine the exact mileage to be electrified in Control Period 5 once the development of all the projects and programmes to be delivered by 2019 has reached a sufficient level of maturity.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-18T16:06:51.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444288/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444288/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444288/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","Railways: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 11 January 2015 to Question 21125, what estimate he has made of the remaining track that will be electrified in connection with the programmes and projects that will go ahead for delivery by 2019 and were referred to in that Answer.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","22103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444289","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-19","<p>The most recent passenger forecasts for the rail network are published in the December 2014 National Policy Statement for National Networks (NPS)<sup><sup>[1]</sup></sup>. A summary of these forecasts is shown below:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="4"><p><strong>Table 2: Growth in Passenger km (in %) since 2011 including Phase 1</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2020</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2026</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2033</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London &amp; South East</p></td><td><p>20.4%</p></td><td><p>31.2%</p></td><td><p>46.1%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Long distance</p></td><td><p>12.9%</p></td><td><p>36.8%</p></td><td><p>63.8%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Regional</p></td><td><p>8.7%</p></td><td><p>16.5%</p></td><td><p>32.8%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total (average)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>15.3%</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>30.5%</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>50.1%</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Network Modelling Framework (NMF) – estimates based on model runs conducted in October 2014. HS2 forecasts have been supplied by HS2 Ltd modelling team and incorporated as overlays to the NMF numbers.</p><br /><p>These can be compared against Office of Rail and Road (ORR) figures<sup><sup>[2]</sup></sup> for existing rail usage for the financial year 2014-15:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Sector</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of passenger kilometres travelled (billions)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>London &amp; South East</p></td><td><p>29.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Long Distance</p></td><td><p>20.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Regional</p></td><td><p>12.0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>62.4</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>The Department for Transport (DfT) is currently undergoing an extensive update of the models involved in forecasting rail demand, specifically in preparation for the Control Period 6 planning. The update will ensure more recent evidence and data are taken into account whilst also ensuring wider consistency with separate modelling being conducted on the High Speed Rail (HSR). Later in 2016 DfT will be in a position to make another publication of forecasts ready for CP6.</p><br /><p>Given the nature of the model, a 10-year successive forecast for rail is not published.</p><br /> <br /><p><sup><sup>[1]</sup></sup> <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/387222/npsnn-print.pdf%20%202.28" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/387222/npsnn-print.pdf 2.28</a> to 2.41</p><p><sup><sup>[2]</sup></sup> https://dataportal.orr.gov.uk/displayreport/report/html/34856085-cf9c-4e0d-a7f8-8f9e5ee1b772</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-19T16:43:34.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444289/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444289/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444289/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","Railways: Passengers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the number of passengers forecast to use the rail network in each of the next 10 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","22093"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444290","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-18","<p>No estimate has been made, though officials are considering how to do so.</p><br /><p>Customers on this part of the rail network haven’t always received the service they deserve. When we awarded the franchise through our robust competitive process we bought a plan to deliver a high quality service for passengers which will deliver more services, more capacity and three new fleets of trains on the Govia Thameslink Railway. None of this comes without short term challenges as a result of this significant four year programme of transformation. We believe that this plan alongside the Government’s investment in the Thameslink programme will deliver the improvements passengers deserve.</p><br /><p>I am concerned about ensuring passengers receive the best possible service during the present crucial works on this part of the rail network. Shortly after the election I set up the South East Quadrant Taskforce, which I continue to chair. This group, which includes Network Rail and Govia Thameslink Railway, is absolutely committed to making improvements and, crucially, to making sure that rail customers see the benefits of these improvements.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-18T16:32:24.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444290/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444290/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444290/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","Railways: Sussex","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the economic effect of delays to rail services into London Victoria from the Sussex coast in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","22121"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444291","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-18","<p>This data has never been collected, but consideration is being given to how to do so across the network.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-18T16:23:30.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444291/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444291/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444291/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","Railways: Sussex","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the total amount of time passengers were delayed on rail services from the Sussex coast into London Victoria in 2015.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","22120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444292","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-19","<p>We are absolutely committed to ensuring that the South West has the best infrastructure possible and we are determined to do everything possible to stop damage like we saw in 2014 happening again. That is why we have invested £31 million into improving the resilience of rail routes in the South West, and Network Rail spent £40 million on repairing and strengthening the line at Dawlish after the extreme weather.</p><br /><p>We are working with the rail industry and the Peninsula Rail Task Force as they explore the potential for longer-term improvements in the area, including the premise of additional routes to the current mainline route via Dawlish.</p><br />","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-19T16:32:39.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444292/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444292/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444292/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","Railways: Okehampton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent steps he has taken to extend railway network services between London and Okehampton.","false","Biography information for Mr Geoffrey Cox","Torridge and West Devon","Mr Geoffrey Cox","22085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444293","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-18","<p>There were 17 expressions of interest applications in phase 1 of the Advanced Biofuels Demonstration Competition, of which six projects were shortlisted and invited to submit a phase 2 application.</p><br /><p>Three winning projects were offered the following grants alongside significant private sector investment. Grant instalments will be paid subject to various conditions and the achievement of specified milestones:</p><ul><li>Advanced Plasma Power Ltd (Go Green Fuels) [Swindon]: £11 million to upscale the production of advanced biofuels from household waste</li><li>Celtic Renewables Ltd [Edinburgh]: £11 million to expand the production of advanced biofuels from scotch whisky residues</li><li>Nova Pangaea Technologies Ltd [Teeside]: £3 million to develop the process of producing advanced biofuels from forestry biomass (plant matter).</li></ul><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-18T13:24:31.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444293/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444293/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444293/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","Biofuels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many applicants there were to the Advanced Biofuel Demonstration Competition; how many such applicants were successful; and what funding under what structure each successful applicant received.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","22116"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444294","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-20","<p>We do not hold estimates of the cost of reviewing the findings and conclusions of the Airport Commission’s report.</p><br />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-01-20T14:04:23.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444294/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444294/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444294/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","Airports Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the estimated cost to his Department has been of evaluating the Airports Commission's Final Report since 1 July 2015.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","22175"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444295","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-18","<p>We receive representations on a number of issues from the Mayor of London, and this has included the impact of the increasing number of private hire vehicles in London on congestion, air quality and parking issues on London’s road network.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-18T11:06:36.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444295/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444295/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444295/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","Taxis: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he has received representations from the Mayor of London on his concerns about the number of private hire vehicles being licensed each month in London.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","22142"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444296","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-19","<p>I refer the Honourable Member to my answer of 11<sup>th</sup> January 2016 (UIN 20996) <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=QuestionsWithAnswersOnly&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=20996" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=QuestionsWithAnswersOnly&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=20996</a>.</p><br />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-01-19T16:19:25.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444296/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444296/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444296/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","London Airports: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has conducted a comparative assessment of the loss of life as a result of an aircraft crashing on approach or arrival at Heathrow and Gatwick airports.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","22134"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444297","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-18","<p>This Government does not intend to amend primary legislation to allow the number of private hire vehicles licensed in London or elsewhere to be restricted.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-18T11:10:07.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444297/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444297/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444297/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","Taxis: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to provide the Mayor of London with the powers to place a cap on private hire vehicles in London.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","22143"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444298","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-19","<p>The Bus Service Operators Grant (BSOG) is paid to operators based in England on a fixed rate of £0.3457 per litre and is no longer directly linked to fuel duty. As a result, changes in fuel costs should not have any direct impact on the uptake of BSOG. We will be publishing more details of our plans to reform BSOG later this year.</p><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-19T16:23:49.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444298/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444298/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444298/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","Bus Service Operators Grant","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department plans to take account of lower fuel costs in its reform of the Bus Service Operators Grant.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","22133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444299","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-18","<p>HS2 Ltd have carried out an extensive reviews of tunnel boring rates for comparable forms of tunnel (looking at the size of tunnel and type of tunnel boring machine used) as part of the work for the hybrid Bill development, including tunnels both in this country and overseas. Particular attention has been made to ascertaining the ‘hard average rate’ achieved on these tunnels, which is much more appropriate in calculating the overall time to complete a particular tunnel drive for its entire length from &quot;machine in to machine out&quot;. HS2 Ltd have provided evidence from these applicable tunnel projects in front of the Select Committee and explained on several occasions how the tunnel drive rates from these other projects support the current assumed drive rate for the HS2 Chiltern Tunnel. No further review is considered to be required as there is no further appropriate evidence available.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-01-18T15:28:52.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444299/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444299/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444299/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether a further review of the tunnel boring machine advance rates for the High Speed 2 Chiltern tunnel has yet taken place.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","22205"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444300","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-18","<p>North Yorkshire County Council are continuing their assessment of the damage to Tadcaster Bridge as the water levels reduce, and they are also removing debris. We have not asked the Council for an estimate of repairs to date at Tadcaster Bridge as they work on a County wide assessment of damage to road and bridge infrastructure.</p><br /><p>The Government recently announced funding of £3.3m to repair Tadcaster Bridge and for a temporary footbridge to reconnect the community, none of which has come from the Road Investment Strategy as that is funding for the Strategic Road Network managed by Highways England.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-18T13:35:47.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444300/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444300/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444300/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","Tadcaster Bridge: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 11 January 2016 to Question 21012, what repairs there have been to Tadcaster Bridge to date; and whether finance for any repairs will be found from (a) the Road Investment Strategy and (b) a contingency fund.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","22216"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444301","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-18","<p>Network Rail advises that it has not yet finalised the estimated full repair costs and the associated Schedule 4 network possessions compensation payments. The company’s estimates remain subject to potential variation to the method of repair and to compensation claims from the train operators.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2016-01-18T15:45:15.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444301/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444301/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444301/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","Railways: South Lanarkshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the full costs of repairing the Lamington Viaduct will be met by Network Rail's insurance cover.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","22202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444302","Department for Transport","false","2016-01-18","<p>In accordance with the requirements of the draft Northern Franchise Agreement published on 27th February 2015, the new Northern franchisee will establish a North East Business Unit for rail services by the end of June 2016.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-01-18T11:21:54.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444302/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444302/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/444302/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-01-12","Railways: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps the new Northern franchisee will take to establish a North East Business Unit for rail services.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","22203"
